 "cells": [

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-part1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Warm-Up\n",
    "\n",
    "These cells test your understanding of lambda syntax and functional interfaces **without requiring you to write much code**.\n",
    "Read carefully, predict the output, then run to check."
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Exercise 1a — Fix the broken lambdas\n",
    "\n",
    "Each cell below contains one broken lambda. Fix the syntax error and run the cell to confirm it passes.\n",
    "Every case demonstrates a different rule — read the comment before editing."
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1a-i",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**1a-i** — Explicit type on a single parameter requires parentheses around the parameter list."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-1a-i",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.function.*;\n",
    "\n",
    "Function<String, Integer> lenOf = String s -> s.length();  // BROKEN\n",
    "\n",
    "// --- do not edit below ---\n",
    "assert lenOf.apply(\"hello\") == 5 : \"lenOf(hello) should be 5\";\n",
    "System.out.println(\"1a-i passed!\");"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1a-ii",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**1a-ii** — Two parameters always require parentheses around the parameter list, even when types are omitted."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-1a-ii",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.function.*;\n",
    "\n",
    "BiFunction<Integer, Integer, Integer> add = a, b -> a + b;  // BROKEN\n",
    "\n",
    "// --- do not edit below ---\n",
    "assert add.apply(3, 4) == 7 : \"add(3, 4) should be 7\";\n",
    "System.out.println(\"1a-ii passed!\");"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1a-iii",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**1a-iii** — You cannot mix typed and untyped parameters. Either all parameters have explicit types, or none do."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-1a-iii",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.function.*;\n",
    "\n",
    "BiFunction<String, Integer, String> repeat = (String s, n) -> s.repeat(n);  // BROKEN\n",
    "\n",
    "// --- do not edit below ---\n",
    "assert repeat.apply(\"ab\", 3).equals(\"ababab\") : \"repeat(ab, 3) should be ababab\";\n",
    "System.out.println(\"1a-iii passed!\");"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1a-iv",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**1a-iv** — A block body (with curly braces) requires an explicit `return` statement when the functional interface's method returns a value."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-1a-iv",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.function.*;\n",
    "\n",
    "Function<Integer, Integer> triple = x -> { x * 3; };  // BROKEN\n",
    "\n",
    "// --- do not edit below ---\n",
    "assert triple.apply(7) == 21 : \"triple(7) should be 21\";\n",
    "System.out.println(\"1a-iv passed!\");"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1a-v",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**1a-v** — A block body requires a semicolon after the last statement before the closing brace."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-1a-v",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.function.*;\n",
    "\n",
    "Predicate<String> isEmpty = s -> { return s.isEmpty() };  // BROKEN\n",
    "\n",
    "// --- do not edit below ---\n",
    "assert isEmpty.test(\"\")    : \"isEmpty(\\\"\\\") should be true\";\n",
    "assert !isEmpty.test(\"hi\") : \"isEmpty(hi) should be false\";\n",
    "System.out.println(\"1a-v passed!\");"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1a-vi",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**1a-vi** — The lambda body must match the return type of the functional interface. `Consumer<T>`'s `accept` method returns `void`, so the body should *do something* with the value rather than return it. This lambda is called `printer` — what might a printer do with a String?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-1a-vi",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.function.*;\n",
    "\n",
    "Consumer<String> printer = s -> { return s; };  // BROKEN\n",
    "\n",
    "// --- do not edit below ---\n",
    "printer.accept(\"test\");  // should run without throwing\n",
    "System.out.println(\"1a-vi passed!\");"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Exercise 1b — Choosing the right functional interface\n",
    "\n",
    "Match each lambda to a predefined functional interface from `java.util.function`.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task:** Replace each `???` with the correct interface type (`Supplier`, `Consumer`, `Predicate`, `Function`, `BiFunction`, or `BiConsumer`).\n",
    "\n",
    "You do **not** need to change the lambda expressions themselves."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-1b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.function.*;\n",
    "\n",
    "// Takes a String, returns its uppercased version\n",
    "???<String, String> toUpper = s -> s.toUpperCase();\n",
    "\n",
    "// Takes an Integer, returns true if it is even\n",
    "???<Integer> isEven = n -> n % 2 == 0;\n",
    "\n",
    "// Takes no argument, returns the string \"hello\"\n",
    "???<String> greeter = () -> \"hello\";\n",
    "\n",
    "// Takes a String, prints it, returns nothing\n",
    "???<String> printer = s -> System.out.println(\">> \" + s);\n",
    "\n",
    "// Takes two Integers, returns their product\n",
    "???<Integer, Integer, Integer> multiply = (a, b) -> a * b;\n",
    "\n",
    "// --- do not edit below this line ---\n",
    "assert toUpper.apply(\"java\").equals(\"JAVA\")  : \"toUpper failed\";\n",
    "assert isEven.test(4)                        : \"isEven(4) should be true\";\n",
    "assert !isEven.test(7)                       : \"isEven(7) should be false\";\n",
    "assert greeter.get().equals(\"hello\")         : \"greeter failed\";\n",
    "printer.accept(\"test\");\n",
    "assert multiply.apply(3, 4) == 12            : \"multiply(3,4) should be 12\";\n",
    "System.out.println(\"1b passed!\");"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Exercise 1c — Predict the output\n",
    "\n",
    "**Before running** this cell, read the stream pipeline carefully and write down what you expect `result` to be.\n",
    "\n",
    "Then run the cell. Were you right?\n",
    "\n",
    "Think about: what does each intermediate operation do to the stream? In what order does the `filter` remove elements?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-1c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.*;\n",
    "import java.util.stream.*;\n",
    "\n",
    "List<String> words = List.of(\"banana\", \"apple\", \"cherry\", \"apricot\", \"blueberry\");\n",
    "\n",
    "long result = words.stream()\n",
    "    .filter(w -> w.startsWith(\"a\"))\n",
    "    .count();\n",
    "\n",
    "// Write your prediction as a comment here before running:\n",
    "// My prediction: result = ???\n",
    "\n",
    "System.out.println(\"result = \" + result);"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-1d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Exercise 1d — Effectively final\n",
    "\n",
    "The method below does **not** compile.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task:** Read the error, understand why the lambda capture is invalid, and fix it with the smallest possible change — without removing the lambda or the assertion.\n",
    "\n",
    "Hint: what does the lecture say about local variables used inside a lambda body? Does `limit` qualify?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-1d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.function.*;\n",
    "import java.util.*;\n",
    "import java.util.stream.*;\n",
    "\n",
    "// Do not move code outside this method.\n",
    "List<Integer> filterAbove(List<Integer> values) {\n",
    "    int limit = 5;\n",
    "    limit = 10;  // this reassignment makes `limit` non-final\n",
    "    Predicate<Integer> bigEnough = n -> n > limit;\n",
    "    return values.stream().filter(bigEnough).collect(Collectors.toList());\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "// --- do not edit below ---\n",
    "var result = filterAbove(List.of(3, 7, 12, 9, 2, 11));\n",
    "assert result.equals(List.of(12, 11)) : \"Expected [12, 11] but got \" + result;\n",
    "System.out.println(\"1d passed! result = \" + result);"
   ]
  },

