  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "md-3d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Exercise 3d — `collect` to a different form: joining strings\n",
    "\n",
    "You can collect into things other than a list. `Collectors.joining(delimiter)` is a terminal collector that concatenates all stream elements into one `String`.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task:** From the list of names below, build a pipeline that:\n",
    "1. Filters out all names that don't start with `\"A\"`\n",
    "2. Sorts alphabetically\n",
    "3. Collects them into a single comma-separated string, meaning `\",\"` is the delimiter\n",
    "\n",
    "Expected result: `\"Alice,Anna,Arthur\"`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "code-3d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import java.util.*;\n",
    "import java.util.stream.*;\n",
