    "### Exercise 3f ⭐ — Challenge: multi-step transformation\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the most complex exercise. Take your time.\n",
    "\n",
    "You are given a list of CSV-style strings, each representing a student's name and score:\n",
    "```\n",
    "[\"Alice:82\", \"Bob:91\", \"Clara:58\", \"David:74\", \"Eva:91\", \"Frank:63\"]\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Write a pipeline that:\n",
    "1. Splits each string on `\":\"` to get the score part\n",
    "2. Parses the score as an `int`\n",
    "3. Keeps only scores **≥ 70**\n",
    "4. Returns the **average** of those scores as a `double`\n",
    "\n",
    "Passing scores: 82, 91, 74, 91 → average = `(82+91+74+91)/4 = 84.5`\n",
    "\n",
    "Hints:\n",
    "- `\"Alice:82\".split(\":\")[1]` gives `\"82\"`\n",
    "- Use `mapToInt(...)` instead of `map(...)` for the parsing step — unlike `map`, `mapToInt` converts the stream to an `IntStream`, which gives you access to numeric operations like `average()`\n",
    "- `average()` returns an `OptionalDouble` — call `.getAsDouble()` to retrieve it."
   ]
